parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause extended stopping distances, loss of vehicle control, and increased risk of accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light illuminates on the dashboard
the vehicle surges or pulses when braking
the brakes fail to engage or engage intermittently
the vehicle slides or pulls to one side when braking
and the stopping distance is extended.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Extends to Floor or Fails to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal to engage or extending to the floor can cause loss of vehicle control, extended stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal extends to the floor
the brakes fail to engage or engage intermittently
and the stopping distance is extended.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration and warping of the brakes can cause loss of vehicle control, extended stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brakes vibrate or pulse when applied
the rotors warp or become uneven
and the stopping distance is extended.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and blowout can cause loss of steering capability, maneuverability, and control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
Tire delamination and failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
Tire sidewall failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Issues with the fuel system, such as leaks or faulty sensors, can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The loss of power and hesitation can cause the vehicle to suddenly slow down, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
